🗑️ Delete the Netlify Site

1. Go to app.netlify.com and log in
2. Click on your site (the one linked to docker.github.io)
3. Go to Site configuration (left sidebar)
4. Scroll all the way to the bottom to Danger zone
5. Click Delete this site
6. It will ask you to type the site name to confirm — type it and hit Delete


Done in ~30 seconds. Immediate and irreversible.

---

🗑️ Delete the GitHub Repo

⚠️ Before you continue, double-check that you are deleting the correct repository. Deletion is immediate and irreversible.

1. Go to github.com/<your-org-or-username>/<your-repo>
2. Click Settings (top tab bar, far right)
3. Scroll to the bottom — Danger Zone section
4. Click Delete this repository
5. GitHub will ask you to type <your-org-or-username>/<your-repo> to confirm
6. Enter your password or confirm with 2FA if prompted


Also immediate and irreversible.

